Blocks.Text: We build upon PCS [8] and perform in-domain contrastive learning and cross-domain self-supervised
Memory bank features are updated with a momentum of 0.5
Spherical K-means [9] (K=2500) is used to cluster memory bank features into prototypes
Our objective function comprises the in-domain and cross-domain losses from PCS, all losses from UFLD,
and our pseudo loss for grid-based lane detection
